description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to join the ICT Clinical Systems support team at Cwm Taf Morgannwg University Health Board. A typical candidate will have interest in ICT as well as experience in supporting ICT applications and devices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will encompass both national and local systems and working on projects and upgrades in collaboration with other health boards and NWIS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the service delivery of the clinical information systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recognise and influence service improvements through user engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as an advocate for and to promote best practice with regard to the clinical information systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop modern working practices, maximising benefits from clinical systems and their interaction with other clinical and hospital system/devices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be responsible for formulating and monitoring policies and protocols to support the clinical information systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with multiple stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support a small team of support staff within ICT and work alongside other system managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the service support team in order to design and implement an effective support model&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in managing systems within an NHS setting will be required for this role and you will be responsible for ICT clinical system areas such as Pathology &amp; Cardiology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to support system upgrades, liaising with the infrastructure team, NWIS and the end users by communicating effectively and also assist in user acceptance testing. You will act as first point of contact to clinical departments relating to ICT incidents and issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Typically the Systems Support team handle the day to day operations of the departments and include clinical decision making and patient care systems in use on wards and in clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be expected to participate in an on-call rota and the ability to travel between sites across the health board is an essential part of the post&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
